Package comp127graphics.events

Enum Key

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Key>
      • comp127graphics.events.Key
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Key>, java.lang.constant.Constable
    public enum Key
extends java.lang.Enum<Key>
    A key on the keyboard. Note that this represents the key itself, not the character the user typed. For example, if the user types an exclamation point, the KeyEvent the app receives will be NUM_1 with a SHIFT modifier.
    See Also:
    KeyboardEvent
